Package oracle.nosql.driver.values

Class FieldFinder.MapWalker

  • java.lang.Object
    • oracle.nosql.driver.values.FieldFinder.MapWalker
  • Enclosing class:
    FieldFinder
    public static class FieldFinder.MapWalker
extends Object
    A class that allows a caller to walk an NSON MAP using a "pull" pattern. The ByteInputStream used for construction must be positioned on an NSON MAP. Each call to next() moves the state forward. The value of each map entry must be consumed by the caller either by reading it or skipping it by calling skip(). A typical usage pattern is: 
       MapWalker walker = new MapWalker(stream);
   while (walker.hasNext()) {
       walker.next();
       String name = walker.getName(); // returns name of current element
       // read or skip value
       if (name.equals("interesting_int")) {
           Nson.readNsonInt(stream);
       else {
           walker.skip();
       }
   }

        public void skip()
          throws IOException

        IOException - if there's a problem with the stream
